// Min, Max, Length and Average of an array of numbers - JAYSON
/*
Initialize an array of numbers
1. Initialize an array of numbers
2. Set the minimum value to the first element of the array
3. Set the maximum value to the first element of the array
4. Set the total value to 0
5. Iterate over each element of the array
6. If the current element is less than the minimum value, set the minimum value to the current element
7. If the current element is greater than the maximum value, set the maximum value to the current element
8. Add the current element to the total value
9. After iterating over all elements, divide the total value by the length of the array to get the average value
10.Output the minimum value, maximum value, array length, and average value of the numbers.
*/